       }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:53c5832a-eecc-4d6b-a4c3-d1b78a430dca\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"unknown\",\n      \"label\": \"Cron: Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\",\n      \"displayName\": \"Cron: Daily Briefing 5AM UTC+7\",\n      \"updatedAt\": 1776031202690,\n      \"sessionId\": \"b8428c5a-6da6-4dbe-9615-52a4570a78a5\",\n      \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 200000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 35262,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0,\n      \"systemSent\": true,\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/b8428c5a-6da6-4dbe-9615-52a4570a78a5.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"thinking\",\n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\nidation\\n   - Uses encrypted data for FE attendance\\n\\n4. **Checkins module:**\\n   - Good separation between Schedule and Abnormal checkin\\n   - validateCreatorInParticipants is a private method\\n   - Good validation of time constraints\\n   - Overall clean architecture\\n\\n5. **OKRs module:**\\n   - Extremely complex aggregation pipeline in getOKRByFilter - lots of nested logic\\n   - No DRY violations detected\\n   - Good RBAC\\n\\n6. **Leave Requests module:**\\n   - 656 lines in leaveRequests.service.ts - VERY LARGE\\n   - Two-level approval workflow (Manager + HR)\\n   - Good leave balance management\\n   - Good notification system\\n   - Some DRY issues: repeated employee lookup, approval logic patterns\\n\\n7. **Auth module:**\\n   - Good token management (access + refresh)\\n   - Cookie-based refresh token\\n   - Solid implementation overall\\n\\n8. **Roles/Permissions module:**\\n   - Proper use of transactions for consistency\\n   - Redis caching for permissions with cache-busting on updates\\n   - Service instantiates itself with PermissionService.callingPermissionMaps preventing race conditions\\n\\n9. **Niko modules:**\\n   - Emotion: Good service\\n\\n, well-structured\\n   - Orders: Uses transactions properly for complex operations\\n   - Wallets: Good balance tracking\\n   - Criteria: Has try-catch with generic error rethrow - not ideal\\n   - Gifts: Good but has hardcoded 'PENDING' string (magic number)\\n   - Cart: Clean service\\n\\n**FE (React/TypeScript/RTK Query):**\\n\\n1. **API files:**\\n   - Good use of RTK Query with providesTags/invalidatesTags\\n   - Some use of `any` types (attendanceApi, okrApi, leaveApi)\\n   - Proper use of overrideExisting\\n\\n2. **AccountPage.tsx:**\\n   - 413 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Good separation of concerns with multiple forms\\n   - Clean TypeScript usage\\n   - No loading states, error handling, or prop drilling issues\\n\\n3. **EmployeePage.tsx:**\\n   - 311 lines - reasonable size\\n   - Clean patterns with hooks like usePermission, AccessControl\\n   - Good use of memoization\\n\\n4. **NikoPage.tsx:**\\n   - 779 lines - VERY LARGE, should be split into sub-components\\n   - Hardcoded emotion data in component (should be from API)\\n   - EMOTION_MAP created in render body\\n\\nNow I'm identifying the critical issues. The attendance module has massive code duplication across multiple files, the leaveRequests service is oversized at 656 lines, and there are hardcoded magic strings scattered throughout. The NikoPage component at 779 lines needs refactoring into smaller pieces. Beyond that, I'm seeing `any` types leaking across the FE API files, missing JSDoc comments in most places, and inconsistent error handling with empty catch blocks in some niko services. There's also mixed language usage between Vietnamese and English that should be standardized, and some files have unnecessary complexity that could be simplified.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Now I have enough data to write the comprehensive code quality report. Let me create it:\\n\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"toolCall\",\n              \"id\": \"call_function_4mi0q9it66m6_1\",\n              \"name\": \"exec\",\n              \"arguments\": {\n                \"command\": \"mkdir -p /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/reviews\"\n              }\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV-Holding-DEV\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 5824,\n            \"output\": 924,\n            \"totalTokens\": 101731,\n            \"cacheRead\": 89378,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 5605,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1775982347614,\n          \"responseId\": \"062a8a0d36758ec7975bb77b6a44b7d6\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"3f484677\",\n            \"seq\": 136\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}[... 78885 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"count":22,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","kind":"other","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-agent-master-orchestrator-telegram-direct-6053576134","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:6053576134","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1776055821034,"sessionId":"7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":104503,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776055820720,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"telegram","lastTo":"telegram:6053576134","lastAccountId":"main_bot","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/7ae3b683-0b91-4427-abbe-b78ef94eb140.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great news! The cron runs show that the DTLX cron is actually working again! Looking at the most recent runs:\n\n1. **04:34 UTC** - `status: ok` ✅ - Delivered to group -5168104492\n2. **04:32 UTC** - `status: ok` ✅ - Delivered to group -5168104492\n\nThe cron is back! The timeout issue was fixed when I increased it to 300s. The latest run at 04:34 was successful.\n\nHowever, Lead is asking specifically about the group `-5168104492` not working. The cron IS delivering to that group now. But Lead might mean that the master-orchestrator isn't responding to messages in that group. \n \nI'm seeing multiple sessions for this group—one from April 12 that's still running with active subagents handling a settings page rebuild and FE refactoring. There's also a separate Telegram session for the same group, but the status is unclear since the session list timed out. The cron is working and delivering reports, but I need to figure out what specifically isn't functioning for the group itself. which is `-5163901258` according to the session. The cron DTLX reports to `-5168104492` (the QLHV group) but there's actually a different session for the DTLX ecosystem group at `-5163901258`.\n\nWait, I had updated MEMORY.md to say DTLX group is `-5168104492`. But there's also a separate session `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` which is labeled as `telegram:g-ahv-dtlx-ecosystem`. This is confusing.\n\nThe cron job for DTLX (6f3323ef) is delivering to `-5168104492` (QLHV group), but there's a separate group session with the old DTLX ID `-5163901258` that's still active and running subagents.\n\nI need to clarify which group the Lead is actually referring to, since `-5168104492` appears to be the QLHV group based on its label, while `-5163901258` seems to be the actual DTLX ecosystem group where work is happening."},{"type":"text","text":"Tin tốt Lead! **Cron DTLX đã hoạt động lại** ✅\n\nVừa thấy trong run history:\n- `04:34 UTC` → ✅ Delivered to `-5168104492` \n- `04:32 UTC` → ✅ Delivered to `-5168104492`\n\nĐã tăng timeout lên 300s và cron tự phục hồi sau gateway restart.\n\nNhưng để chắc chắn, cho Orbis biết: Lead gửi message vào group nào mà không thấy trả lời?\n- `-5168104492` (QLHV ecosystem) — cron đang gửi báo cáo vào đây ✅\n- `-5163901258` (DTLX ecosystem) — session đang chạy riêng cho DTLX"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":13859,"output":659,"totalTokens":105162,"cacheRead":90644,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776055226293,"responseId":"062ba6bc9400dc759a56c88502de5af6","__openclaw":{"id":"ed7485da","seq":94}},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-5163901258 master của chat group này đang làm việc không sao tôi chưa thấy phản hồi"}],"timestamp":1776055820720,"__openclaw":{"id":"0b90b160","seq":95},"senderLabel":"Khương Nịnh (6053576134)"},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lead is asking about the master orchestrator for group -5163901258. Let me check the sessions for this group."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gyqd84u6d2kk_1","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"messageLimit":3}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":53,"totalTokens":104869,"cacheRead":10548,"cacheWrite":94268,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776055820828,"responseId":"062ba90e200b9b3a4874e589b650904e","__openclaw":{"id":"d1353d08","seq":96}}]},{"key":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258","kind":"group","channel":"telegram","origin":{"provider":"telegram","accountId":"main_bot"},"displayName":"telegram:g-ahv-qlhv-ecosystem","deliveryContext":{"channel":"telegram","to":"telegram:-5163901258","accountId":"main_bot"},"updatedAt":1776055787666,"sessionId":"8e0cb2bc-8245-4c89-bc2c-e3cca2257d0f","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":53062,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"sta