:"webchat","label":"Cron: 5p Progress Report - DTLX","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-master-orchestrator-cron-6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1776056040866,"sessionId":"0683399d-16cc-4dfa-96f8-fd9eeb2c64fd","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":39620,"estimatedCostUsd":0,"status":"running","startedAt":1776051624913,"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"/root/.openclaw/agents/master-orchestrator/sessions/0683399d-16cc-4dfa-96f8-fd9eeb2c64fd.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The memory lookup failed (no baseline state stored). Let me analyze the current sessions state and compare against what I know from the session history to detect changes.\n\n**Current active sessions (status: running):**\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — running (direct message, current session)\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — running (this cron session itself)\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` — running (QLHV group, with 2 child subagents: senior-backend + senior-frontend)\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — running (5p main cron)\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:main` — running (heartbeat session, but with error)\n\nI notice the QLHV group session has two failed subagents that were spawned earlier, and there are also some failed prompt-optimizer sessions in the mix.\n\nLooking at the failed sessions across the ecosystem, I can see the backend and frontend subagents for QLHV both failed recently, and there's a DTLX group session that ended after working on a settings page. The session details show the status check came through on time, but I'm realizing this cron instance is essentially checking itself—it was triggered at 04:54 UTC and the sessions_list output shows it's currently running, which is what we'd expect. I'm not seeing significant state changes in the ecosystem since the last report at 03:23 UTC—the same 5 cron sessions are active, the pre-existing subagent failures remain unchanged, and the main orchestrator session is still running with that known error. The only notable activity is the QLHV group session doing GitLab pipeline work and running builds, which was already in progress. I'm seeing a key difference in the QLHV group session's activity - it's now running `yarn build` verification, which suggests it's progressed from the earlier pipeline polling stage. The direct message from Khương arrived just 4 seconds ago, so the session is still very much active and responding. the direct message and the group session running `yarn build` are the two significant changes since the last report. The QLHV group session was mentioned as \"running\" in the previous baseline, but now I can see it's actively building—plus the Lead's direct request about monitoring active agents adds another meaningful shift to track."},{"type":"text","text":"🟡 Orbis-DTLX — 5p Update | 04:54 UTC 13 Apr\n\nChanges detected:\n• Lead (Khương) messaged Orbis directly — asked for master agent status updates (active sessions, task details)\n• QLHV group session (`-5163901258`) now running `yarn build` verification — progressing from pipeline polling to build step\n• QLHV group subagents (senior-backend + senior-frontend) still in failed state from earlier run — unchanged baseline\n\nPipeline: **DEGRADED**\n• Active sessions: 5 (Orbis direct ✅ | DTLX cron ✅ | QLHV cron ✅ | QLHV group ✅ | main heartbeat ⚠️)\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: ⚠️ QLHV subagent failures (pre-existing, no new failures)\n\n— Orbis 🌐"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":25549,"output":735,"totalTokens":40355,"cacheRead":13668,"cacheWrite":403,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776056088642,"responseId":