{"type":"message","id":"d563f2e9","parentId":"db4dbb8d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:00:58.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `openclaw cron` command is timing out. This is the same issue as before — the gateway might not be responding to CLI commands quickly. Let me try a different approach.\n\nActually, the key issue here is that the QLHV cron (ed2d0b5d) has `stopReason: aborted` in its last sequence. This means it's trying to send to the Telegram group but getting aborted each time.\n\nLooking at the cron session history:\n- Sequence 5: `stopReason: aborted`, `errorMessage: \"Request was aborted.\"`\n\nThis is a timeout. The cron is trying to send a message to the Telegram group, taking too long, and getting aborted. \n\nThe pattern is becoming clearer — the cron successfully triggered and started, but when it tries to deliver the report to the group, it times out and gets aborted. Yet it's still marked as running, which suggests the gateway is retrying the delivery. This would explain why Lead received the report, even though the cron session itself shows as aborted.\n\nLooking at the sequence of events, the cron ran around 04:47 and appeared to fail, but then somehow the report still got sent to Lead's Telegram at 04:55. I'm realizing the cron might have actually succeeded in delivering to Lead's direct session despite the `stopReason: aborted` status in its own session context. The cron is supposed to check the previous state and only send if there are changes, so it likely detected the new QLHV group session and triggered a send to Lead's direct session. Looking at the session metadata, the delivery context shows webchat, which seems odd for a Telegram-based cron job—I need to understand how the cron actually routes its messages to different channels.\n\nThe cron is definitely running and sending reports to Lead's Telegram, but the real problem is the QLHV cron for the group at -5168104492 keeps getting aborted. The issue seems to be that when it tries to send a message to that group, something interrupts the request and causes it to fail.\n\nLet me trace through the session history to see what's actually happening when it tries to deliver the report.","thinkingSignature":"de46452b58a2ca00bdfd7fe64818427aca78d543c14beef8f20c47c33b960ba7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1sh02nvg70zf_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7","limit":2}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":183,"output":505,"cacheRead":33235,"cacheWrite":350,"totalTokens":34273,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056446136,"responseId":"062bab7f7181a0a9e2341899b7be1ca9"}}
