{"type":"message","id":"1f329658","parentId":"6c88e410","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:05:26.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a SQLite database for task runs. Let me look at it to understand the cron state. But actually, modifying the SQLite database directly might be risky.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to fix the cron through external means, let me handle the QLHV group reporting differently:\n\n1. The QLHV cron is stuck because the group session has ended\n2. Instead of fixing the cron, I'll create a NEW session for the QLHV group that handles the reporting\n3. Or, I'll modify the HEARTBEAT.md to include the QLHV group reporting in a different cron\n\nActually, let me look at this from the perspective of \"what does Lead actually need?\"Lead wants to receive regular updates about active agents and their status. Currently:\n\n\n- The \"Agent Status to Lead\" cron IS sending these updates every 10 minutes directly to Lead ✅\n- The QLHV cron is supposed to send updates to the QLHV group every 5 minutes, but it's stuck ❌\n\nThe real question is whether the QLHV group cron needs to be fixed at all. Lead receives status updates about the QLHV group from the Agent Status cron, so the dedicated QLHV group cron might be redundant. If the group is active, it handles its own reporting; if it's not, the cron just wastes resources trying to send.\n\nLet me think through the session lifecycle: the QLHV group session is marked as done with a runtime of 9205ms (about 9 seconds), but the cron that was supposed to send to it is stuck. I'm trying to figure out if the session actually ended or if it's still running somehow.\n\nActually, I think I've got it—the session was indeed short-lived at around 9 seconds, and when the cron tried to send a message to it, that failed too, which is why the cron is stuck in a loop. The real solution here is to either prevent the cron from retrying when it can't find the session, or handle that failure more gracefully instead of getting trapped in an infinite retry cycle.\n\nI could try deleting the cron entirely and recreating it, or maybe just respawn it to break the stuck state. Let me check if there's a process flag or state file I can modify to restart it.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to just send a message to the group to recreate its session, which should let the cron break out of its loop on the next run.\n\nWait, that still leaves the underlying issue unresolved—the cron will just fail again in 5 minutes when it can't find the session. The real problem is that the cron needs to handle missing sessions gracefully instead of retrying indefinitely. Let me look at fixing the HEARTBEAT.md logic so the cron can detect when a session doesn't exist and exit cleanly rather than hanging.\n\nThe issue seems to be in how HEARTBEAT.md checks for changes—it's trying to load the heartbeat state file and compare it against the current state, but something in that flow is causing the cron to hang when the session is gone.\n\nLooking at the QLHV cron session, it's been stuck in a running state for about 9 minutes with no messages after the initial one, which suggests the cron is hanging during the sessions_list call itself rather than just failing to find the state file. the cron is hanging during initialization—it's trying to read the state file but getting stuck, possibly because the file is corrupted or the filesystem is slow. Let me try killing and respawning the cron process to see if that clears the blockage.\n\nActually, I realize the cron session itself is stuck, not the gateway scheduler, so killing the CLI process won't help. Let me try using `expect` to automate the `cron delete` command with the right inputs to bypass the interactive prompts.","thinkingSignature":"9341c762cf477d3b59b72498f14db707ebb3eb066ea974c8f137d0436bdcbd09"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8kw8zkho72if_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which expect && expect -v 2>&1 | head -2","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":196,"output":822,"cacheRead":43020,"cacheWrite":2821,"totalTokens":46859,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056706665,"responseId":"062bac83e450f57c75ba2bb31c9978a0"}}
