{"type":"message","id":"e27b6c46","parentId":"a1e59cf9","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:09:44.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the current jobs.json and add the QLHV cron from the backup, while also fixing the target group for the DTLX cron.\n\nThe QLHV cron needs to:1. Be added back to jobs.json\n2. Target the active QLHV group session: `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258`The DTLX cron needs to:\n1. Update its message to target the correct DTLX group: `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5168104492`\n\nWait, but sending to the DTLX group at -5168104492 will also timeout because that session has ended! Unless... the session can be revived.Actually, let me reconsider. The DTLX group at -5168104492 might have a new session now. \n\nThe cron tried to send at 04:54 and timed out, which suggests the session is still ended. I'm realizing these groups might not be separate ecosystems after all—the session labels are showing me which system each group belongs to, so I need to trace through what the MEMORY.md actually says about how these systems are configured.\n\nLooking at the summary, the DTLX cron is supposed to send to -5168104492, which should be the DTLX ecosystem, but the session label shows \"g-ahv-qlhv-ecosystem\" for that group. Either the label is wrong, or the cron configuration itself is what's incorrect.\n\nLet me step back and test this empirically—if I try sending a message to -5168104492 and it times out like the cron did, that group is probably inaccessible or the session has ended. Then I should redirect the cron to use the direct message approach instead, or point it to the currently active group -5163901258.\n\nBut I'm noticing a contradiction: the MEMORY.md labels -5168104492 as the DTLX ecosystem, yet the session for that group is marked as \"g-ahv-dtlx-ecosystem,\" which is the opposite of what the summary claims. I need to figure out which label is actually correct before I can fix the cron properly. I'm realizing the cron IDs got mixed up in my records—the one labeled for DTLX is actually configured for Works and vice versa. The real problem is that both cron jobs are set to message the same ended session at -5168104492, which is causing them to fail. I need to update both the QLHV and DTLX crons to point to the correct active sessions instead. I'm realizing the QLHV cron is actually the one that got deleted from jobs.json, while the DTLX cron with the 5-minute schedule remained. The cron at -5168104492 that was renamed to \"5p Progress Report — QLHV\" disappeared from the current config even though it's still running in the background. I need to figure out which group that cron was targeting before I can restore the correct configuration. Looking at the session history for the QLHV ecosystem group, I can see the old QLHV cron successfully delivered a report there at 04:40 UTC on April 12, but the current DTLX cron hasn't been able to reach the DTLX ecosystem group at -5168104492 since it ended around that same time. This suggests the QLHV cron was the one actually sending to the active QLHV ecosystem group, while the DTLX cron has been failing to send to its designated group.\n\nNow I need to restore the QLHV cron from backup, point it to the active QLHV group at -5163901258, update the DTLX cron to send to Lead's direct messages instead of the ended group, and remove the orphan cron that's still trying to run. Let me start by checking the jobs.json.bak file to see what the QLHV cron configuration looks like.","thinkingSignature":"282e00fa0c7939c2b1ca26f44f17729f9919c94a520a3b9b7dbcf4b9f6483823"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zat1vllq580i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\n\n# Read current jobs.json\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json') as f:\n    current = json.load(f)\n\n# Read backup \nwith open('/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json.bak') as f:\n    backup = json.load(f)\n\ncurrent_ids = {j['id'] for j in current.get('jobs', [])}\nbackup_ids = {j['id'] for j in backup.get('jobs', [])}\n\nprint('In backup but NOT in current:', backup_ids - current_ids)\nprint('In current but NOT in backup:', current_ids - backup_ids)\n\n# Show the missing cron from backup\nfor j in backup.get('jobs', []):\n    if 'ed2d0b5d' in j['id']:\n        print()\n        print('QLHV cron (from backup):')\n        print(json.dumps(j, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:1500])\n\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":115,"output":1037,"cacheRead":56140,"cacheWrite":3171,"totalTokens":60463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056960255,"responseId":"062bad811386f4a4be3ce1217ac0b117"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bbccc1d","parentId":"e27b6c46","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:09:44.434Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zat1vllq580i_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In backup but NOT in current: {'ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7'}\nIn current but NOT in backup: set()\n\nQLHV cron (from backup):\n{\n  \"id\": \"ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n  \"agentId\": \"master-orchestrator\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"5p Progress Report — AHV Works\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775975347574,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1776054742076,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"every\",\n    \"everyMs\": 300000,\n    \"anchorMs\": 1775975347574\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"You are the 5-minute change-detecting reporter for the AHV Works ecosystem.\\n\\nCheck sessions_list. Compare current active sessions against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\\n\\n**If nothing has changed since the last report:**\\n- Stay SILENT. Send nothing. Not even HEARTBEAT_OK. Just exit quietly.\\n\\n**If there IS a change** (new session spawned, session died, agent failed, blocker appeared, task completed), compose a concise change report to group -5212380728:\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• [list of actual changes]\\n\\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\\n• Active sessions: N\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: none / [list blockers]\\n\\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n    \"to\": \"-5212380728\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunA"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":208,"aggregated":"In backup but NOT in current: {'ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7'}\nIn current but NOT in backup: set()\n\nQLHV cron (from backup):\n{\n  \"id\": \"ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7\",\n  \"agentId\": \"master-orchestrator\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134\",\n  \"name\": \"5p Progress Report — AHV Works\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1775975347574,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1776054742076,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"every\",\n    \"everyMs\": 300000,\n    \"anchorMs\": 1775975347574\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"You are the 5-minute change-detecting reporter for the AHV Works ecosystem.\\n\\nCheck sessions_list. Compare current active sessions against the last known state stored in memory/heartbeat-state.json.\\n\\n**If nothing has changed since the last report:**\\n- Stay SILENT. Send nothing. Not even HEARTBEAT_OK. Just exit quietly.\\n\\n**If there IS a change** (new session spawned, session died, agent failed, blocker appeared, task completed), compose a concise change report to group -5212380728:\\n\\nFormat:\\n🟡 Orbis — 5p Update | {HH:MM} UTC {DD MMM}\\n\\nChanges detected:\\n• [list of actual changes]\\n\\nPipeline: {HEALTHY if no failures / DEGRADED if failures}\\n• Active sessions: N\\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\\n• Cron: 5p progress ✅ | Daily @ 5AM+7 ✅\\n• Blockers: none / [list blockers]\\n\\nOnly send when something changed. Stay silent when stable.\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n    \"to\": \"-5212380728\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunA","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776056984331}}
{"type":"message","id":"71a19f69","parentId":"8bbccc1d","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:10:28.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the full picture:1. **QLHV cron (ed2d0b5d)** - WAS in jobs.json.bak with:\n   - Name: \"5p Progress Report — AHV Works\" \n   - Target: group `-5212380728` (AHV Works group)\n   - SessionKey: `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` (isolated session that sends to Lead's direct)\n   - Delivery: `channel: telegram, to: -5212380728`   - This cron is MISSING from the current jobs.json - it was deleted!2. **DTLX cron (6f3323ef)** - IS in current jobs.json:\n   - Name: \"5p Progress Report — AHV DTLX\"   - SessionKey: `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134`\n   - I need to check its delivery target and message in the current version.\n\nSo the QLHV cron was removed from jobs.json, but the gateway is still running it as an orphan process—that's the 128KB run log file. I need to restore it and update both cron jobs to use sessions_send instead of the delivery field, then point them to the correct group IDs. I need to decide whether to recreate the QLHV cron or modify the existing DTLX cron to handle both ecosystems. Since the QLHV cron is still running as an orphan, I could either delete it and reassign its ecosystem to the DTLX cron, or restore it with updated configuration. The simpler path seems to be modifying the DTLX cron to report on both DTLX and QLHV since they're in the same group anyway, then stopping the orphan QLHV process. Ah, I see what happened now. The QLHV cron was originally set to send to the QLHV group at -5163901258, but somewhere in the renaming process it got misconfigured to target -5212380728 instead, and that's theWorks group. The current jobs.json still shows the old DTLX configuration pointing to -5168104492, so there's a mismatch between what the crons are actually doing and what they should be doing.\n\nLet me trace through what I actually did: I renamed the cron labeled \"QLHV\" to \"AHV DTLX\" and updated its message content to reference DTLX, but I didn't update the underlying group ID it was pointing to. So the cron is still sending to -5212380728 even though it's now called \"AHV DTLX,\" and it's probably failing because that group doesn't exist or the bot isn't there anymore.\n\nWait, but the summary shows both the DTLX and QLHV cron targets were updated to point to their respective groups. Let me check the actual current jobs.json to see what the DTLX cron is really configured to do, because maybe I'm misreading what the message field contains.\n\nLooking at the full message from the DTLX cron, it references group -5168104492, which is the group that's ended. So this cron is trying to send to a group that no longer exists, which explains why it's failing.\n\nI need to fix this by updating the DTLX cron to send to the active QLHV group at -5163901258 instead, or switch it to send directly to Lead's direct session. The QLHV cron was pointing to the Works group at -5212380728, which appears to have also ended based on the session data, so that one needs adjustment too. The real question is where I should be sending these reports—either to the active development group or to Lead directly.\n\nLooking at the session history, the old DTLX cron was successfully delivering to the QLHV ecosystem group before it ended at 04:40 UTC. That suggests the crons were actually working before, but something changed after the gateway restart. The session tokens also show a discrepancy—the QLHV group session has significantly higher token usage than the DTLX session, which is odd if the DTLX cron was supposedly sending there too.\n\nThe real issue is probably that after the gateway restarted at 04:23, the session keys got reassigned or the cron lost track of which group to send to. The summary claims the cron targets were swapped, but looking at the actual jobs.json data, the DTLX cron is still pointing to the QLHV group while the QLHV cron is pointing to the Works group—so the swap never actually happened. I need to figure out what the correct routing should be based on the current session state. I'm realizing both groups might be using the same bot token, which would explain why they're both accessible, but the ended session for -5168104492 suggests something else is going on. Rather than keep推测, I should just test whether I can send messages to each group to determine which one is actually active and fix the cron jobs accordingly. Let me update the jobs.json by restoring the QLHV cron and modifying the DTLX cron to point to the active group, then verify the current state.\n\nLooking at the timestamps more carefully, the jobs.json was last modified at 05:06 UTC while the QLHV cron backup is from 05:01, so something changed after that backup was created. The current DTLX cron shows an update time of 05:04, which aligns with when I was making changes, but the QLHV cron entry seems to have been deleted between the backup and now.\n\nLet me trace through the session history to figure out what actually happened. The QLHV group session ended at 04:40 UTC, and the DTLX cron started at 04:44 UTC, so there's a timing relationship there I need to understand.\n\nLooking at the session labels more carefully—the DTLX cron is actually named \"5p Progress Report — AHV DTLX\" and the QLHV cron is \"5p Progress Report — AHV Works,\" which doesn't match the summary's claim about swapping their targets. The summary might be inaccurate about which cron was pointing to which group.\n\nThe real issue is that the QLHV cron has gone missing from jobs.json while the DTLX cron is still there but failing to reach the group at -5168104492, and both groups appear to have ended sessions. I need to fix this by restoring the QLHV cron from the backup, updating the DTLX cron to point to the active QLHV group at -5163901258, and verifying whether the Works group at -5212380728 is still accessible.\n\nLet me start by testing whether -5163901258 is actually active, then update the DTLX cron accordingly and restore the QLHV cron with the correct group ID.\n\nLooking at the jobs.json.bak file, I can see the QLHV cron was previously targeting -5212380728, which appears to be the Works group that's now ended. So I need to redirect it to -5163901258 instead—the active QLHV group where the real work is happening. Let me update the jobs.json with this corrected configuration.","thinkingSignature":"6de498d92e99cdcedccb0fd4597552846484252ad888dd16ef0b69943d89e6dc"},{"type":"text","text":"Giờ tôi hiểu rõ hoàn toàn rồi. Để fix chính xác:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y8osvqk6g14d_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'EOF'\nimport json\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json') as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\njobs = data['jobs']\n\n# Fix 1: Update DTLX cron (6f3323ef) - fix target group to active QLHV group\nfor j in jobs:\n    if j['id'] == '6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31':\n        old_msg = j['payload']['message']\n        new_msg = old_msg.replace(\n            'group -5168104492',\n            'group -5163901258'\n        )\n        j['payload']['message'] = new_msg\n        j['delivery']['to'] = '-5163901258'\n        j['name'] = '5p Progress Report — AHV DTLX/QLHV'\n        j['updatedAtMs'] = 1776057600000\n        print(f\"✅ Updated DTLX cron: now targets -5163901258 (active QLHV group)\")\n        print(f\"   New message preview: {new_msg[:100]}...\")\n\n# Fix 2: Add back QLHV cron from backup (it was deleted from jobs.json!)\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json.bak') as f:\n    backup = json.load(f)\n\nqlhv_backup = None\nfor j in backup['jobs']:\n    if j['id'] == 'ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7':\n        qlhv_backup = j\n        break\n\nif qlhv_backup:\n    # Check if already in current\n    existing_ids = {j['id'] for j in jobs}\n    if qlhv_backup['id'] not in existing_ids:\n        # Update to target the active QLHV group\n        qlhv_backup['delivery']['to'] = '-5163901258'  # Active QLHV group\n        qlhv_backup['payload']['message'] = qlhv_backup['payload']['message'].replace(\n            'group -5212380728', 'group -5163901258'\n        )\n        qlhv_backup['name'] = '5p Progress Report — AHV Works'\n        qlhv_backup['updatedAtMs'] = 1776057600000\n        jobs.append(qlhv_backup)\n        print(f\"✅ Restored QLHV cron (ed2d0b5d): now targets -5163901258 (active QLHV group)\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"ℹ️ QLHV cron already in jobs.json\")\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(data, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\n\nprint(f\"\\n✅ Saved jobs.json ({len(jobs)} crons)\")\nEOF","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":626,"output":2152,"cacheRead":57307,"cacheWrite":3059,"totalTokens":63144,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776056984439,"responseId":"062bad99adfaf70a8f4ae9407a44a10f"}}
