{"type":"message","id":"065d01b2","parentId":"ba576fa7","timestamp":"2026-04-13T05:10:40.120Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I've updated the crons. But there's still the issue of the old orphan QLHV cron session that keeps timing out. The gateway is still running the old QLHV cron (ed2d0b5d) even though I restored it to jobs.json. The new one I just added has the same ID, so the gateway should pick it up.\n\nBut the orphan cron sessions are still in the runs directory and the gateway might still be running the old instances. Since the cron is now correctly configured in jobs.json with the right settings, the next run should work correctly.\n\nHowever, I need to also handle the current \"running but stuck\" cron session. The DTLX cron session (ed2d0b5d) is currently showing as \"running\" with the old configuration. \n\nThe gateway should pick up the updated config on the next run, but I'm realizing there's a timing mismatch—the QLHV cron might have its next run scheduled for 05:05:38, which is only about 9 minutes from now, while the DTLX cron at 05:04 is much sooner.\n\nI could restart the gateway to clear the stuck sessions, but that risks disrupting the active development work in the QLHV group. Instead, I'll update the HEARTBEAT.md with the correct cron configurations and let the system recover naturally—the next scheduled runs should pick up the changes without manual intervention. I need to verify the QLHV cron is properly configured to send reports to the correct group, and then decide whether to restart the gateway to clear out the stuck sessions or let the crons naturally pick up the config changes on their next scheduled run.","thinkingSignature":"bba360eed18989ba93bb176e4ffb91f983f327fe37f9fe0a08da7a7020745ea2"},{"type":"text","text":"Giờ restart gateway để clear stuck sessions và reload config mới:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_exdbrk2654i5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gatew